RATE = 22050

def config_time_axis(ax, num, duration, t0=0):
    def xformat(value, pos):
        return '%.2f' % (value / num * duration + t0)
    ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(plt.FuncFormatter(xformat))
    ax.set_xlabel('Time (seconds)')
    
def gen_wave_title(props):
    s = ''
    s += 'Layer %d' % props['conv_id']
    s += '\n' + ('Residual' if props['mode'] == 'res' else 'Skip') + ' output'
    s += '\nChannels %s' % str(props['channel_ids'])[1:-1]
    return s
    
def display_wave(props, wave):
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, figsize=(10,4), dpi=100)
    
    width = RATE // 30
    mid = len(wave) // 2
    start = mid - width
    end = mid + width
    axes[0].axvline(start, color='r', lw=0.8)
    axes[0].axvline(end, color='r', lw=0.8)
    
    axes[0].set_title('Entire waveform')
    axes[0].set_ylim(-1, 1)
    axes[0].plot(wave)
    config_time_axis(axes[0], len(wave), len(wave) / RATE)

    axes[1].set_title('Zoomed in')
    axes[1].plot(wave[start:end])
    config_time_axis(axes[1], end - start, (end - start) / RATE, t0=start/RATE)
    
    fig.suptitle(gen_wave_title(props), fontsize=14, y=1.2)
    # plt.tight_layout()
    plt.subplots_adjust(hspace=0.7)
    plt.show()
    display(Audio(wave, rate=RATE))

paths = os.listdir()
paths = list(filter(lambda path : path.endswith('.pickle'), paths))
paths = sorted(paths, key=lambda path : int(path.split('.')[0]), reverse=True)
gains = [2, 600, 20, 7, 1]
assert len(paths) == len(gains)
for path, gain in zip(paths, gains):
    props, raw_wave = pickle.load(open(path, 'rb'))
    wave = np.tanh(raw_wave)
    wave = gain * (wave - np.mean(wave))
    display_wave(props, wave)
